ls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nYes... it wasn't over, it still isn't over.\n\n- Nicholas\n|\nDozens of days, experiences, and encounters have set me on a path I never dreamed possible.\n\n- Carlos Wallace, The Other 99 T.Y.M.E.S: Train Your Mind to Enjoy Serenity\n|\nSee, the poor dream all their lives of getting enough to eat and looking like the rich. And what do the rich dream of?? Losing weight and looking like the poor.\n\n- Aravind Adiga, The White Tiger\n|\nI care about you as people, and I believe you are capable of great things. Each of you will contribute something to this world. You are important. You would be missed.\n\n- Cindy\n|\nYou can’t go back and make a new start, but you can start right now and make a brand new ending.\n\n- James R. Sherman, Rejection\n|\nMoney gives you options,Hard work gives you success, Healthy relationships give you a long life, But faith gives you everything!\n\n- Farshad\n|\nAllow your hearts to be driven by principle, not bias. Love, not hate. Unity, not division. The fire of your dreams, not the rain of your sorrows.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nFor a man he get his own ship and his own strong wind, but he cannot stop missing all the passing breezes that never come again.\n\n- Tahar\n|\nThe butterfly counts not months but moments, and has time enough.\n\n- Rabindranath\n|\nThere's a sunrise and a sunset every single day, and they're absolutely free. Don't miss so many of them.\n\n- Jo\n|\nIf you stop learning, you start dying.\n\n- Alin\n|\nWhen your mind is overflowing with peace, you will find peace all around you.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIt's okay to be nervous, scared, angry or sad sometimes so long as you don't let those emotions rule your entire life.\n\n- Avina\n|\nKnowledge that can make miracles happen needs to be guarded carefully. If it falls into the wrong hands, miracles become disasters in no time.\n\n- Pawan Mishra, Coinman: An Untold Conspiracy\n|\nAt breakfast one Saturday I decided to tell Hank my desire to go back to work. He explodes, 'What can you do? You can't make enough to buy your own Kotex\n\n- Martha Lemasters, The Step: One Woman's Journey to Finding Her Own Happiness and Success During the Apollo Space Program\n|\nBuilding something that matters is a marathon, not a sprint.\n\n- Dragos Bratasanu, Ph.D.\n|\nIf you don’t write the book you have to write, everything breaks.\n\n- A.M.\n|\nThe more you remain aware with all the internal and external changes of life, more you allow yourself to move deeper towards the source.\n\n- Roshan\n|\nShe had always thought applying to college would be exciting. Living away from home, meeting so many new people, Learning new things, making a few poor life desicisons....\n\n- Maureen Johnson, 13 Little Blue Envelopes\n|\nBeware of smile, for it is a double edged sword; it cuts the helmet of tension from others head and backfires the peace to yours.\n\n- Vikrmn, Corpkshetra\n|\nOverall, the library held a hushed exultation, as though the cherished volumes were all singing soundlessly within their covers.\n\n- Diana Gabaldon, Outlander\n|\nI'm open to everything. When you start to criticize the times you live in, your time is over.\n\n- Karl\n|\nUsing poise is not being fake; it is being professional, strong, and composed.\n\n- Tanya R. Liverman, In The Mirror: A Woman's Saga\n|\nThere is one spectacle grander than the sea, that is the sky; there is one spectacle grander than the sky, that is the interior of the soul.\n\n- Victor Hugo, Les Misérables\n|\nSerenity is when you get above all this, when it doesn't matter what they think, say or want, but when you do as you are, and see God and Devil as one.\n\n- Henry\n|\nMorning is sweet and always like a beautiful women, evening always shines like a man.\n\n- Biju\n|\nMake nature your best teacher. With great love, learn from her the lessons of life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nAnd even a liar can be scared into telling the truth, same as honest man can be tortured into telling a lie.\n\n- William Faulkner, Light in August\n|\nEarthlings went on being friendly, when they should have been thinking instead.\n\n- Kurt Vonnegut Jr., Breakfast of Champions\n|\nSpiritual learners too slowly graduate like students of normal education. If you are mentally elevated, you can grasp and appreciate complex teachings.\n\n- Girdhar Joshi, Some Mistakes Have No Pardon\n|\nOur sole purpose on this earth is to add value to others. It doesn’t make sense to just exist in people's lives or to be a drain on them, does it?\n\n- Rob\n|\nNo, I am never setting foot in this house again it scares me and makes me sad and I wish you could be a mom whose eyes worked but I don't think you can.\n\n- Laurie Halse Anderson, Wintergirls\n|\nLike Mother Theresa, your greatness unfolds by the kindness you show to the weakest members of humanity.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWater purling between the rocks, weed under the surface like green hair in the wind.\n\n- Mark Haddon, The Red House\n|\nAh, but is it not the mind that is the real grace of Homo sapiens? All the things to think about! All the things to read and appreciate! All the arts! All the things of the spirit!\n\n- Carol Emshwiller, Carmen Dog\n|\nThe written word imparts a gravitas the spoken word lacks. The underlying assumption is that time and thought has been expended on what was written, even if that is not the case.\n\n- Kent Alan Robinson, UnSend: Email, text, and social media disasters...and how to avoid them\n|\nA poem begins as a lump in the throat, a sense of wrong, a homesickness, a lovesickness.\n\n- Robert\n|\nWe have no quarrel with the German nation,One would not quarrel with a flock of sheep.But, generation after generation,They throw up leaders who disturb our sleep.\n\n- Alan\n|\nTo begin a new journey is never easy, but we have to start somewhere to reach a new destination.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI woke in the hour before dawn, stuck in that strange state where the memory of